reviews.text:
5 Stars – Outstanding Work by The Hydro Guys!

The Hydro Guys did a phenomenal job on a very tough project that needed serious attention. The property required extensive cleaning — both on the ground and a full house wash — and they absolutely delivered. From start to finish, they were professional, thorough, and efficient. Every surface looks brand new! I couldn’t be more impressed with the results and highly recommend them to anyone needing power washing services done right. Great job, Hydro Guys!

I just had my first experience with Hydro Guys. We spoke to Alex. He is fantastic and understood our needs and expectations, which they exceeded! Our windows look so clear and clean, with no watermarks! We will be using them again!

I had a great experience with Hydro Guys from start to finish. Quoting over the phone was easy, and they were very professional throughout the entire process. They communicated well about their arrival time and were prompt and courteous. They did an excellent job cleaning off all the mildew, and even went above and beyond to clean all the windows, both upstairs and downstairs. I’m very satisfied with their service and would highly recommend them! Will use them again and recommend them to friends and family.

Photo posted has before (left) and after (right)

Alex and Jomar did an amazing job on the exterior of my house! They cleaned the windows and did a soft wash on all exterior walls. The house looks like new!  They are very professional and considerate. I have already recommended them to 2 neighbors!

These guys did an amazing job! They were on time, gave a fair price and explained the entire process of what to expect during the service and after. Highly recommend to anyone looking to get their roof soft washed!

reviews.text:

Used their services on an upcoming listing. The seller clients were very happy! I called, was quoted over the phone and made appointment. They showed up on time and made sure the job was done right. This company uses the newest technology called "soft wash" the chemicals do the heavy lifting. This takes less time than standard pressure washing, and the results are superior. Overall a Five Star Rating well deserved.

Jose and his team always do an outstanding job! They’ve cleaned our two-story home windows inside and out multiple times, and each time the results are flawless. Professional, reliable, and detail-oriented — I highly recommend Miami Soft Wash for anyone looking to keep their home looking its best.

Their commitment to quality and customer satisfaction is truly commendable. They went above and beyond to ensure every inch was thoroughly cleaned. If you're looking for a reliable, efficient, and friendly roof soft washing service, I highly recommend Miami Soft Wash. They have certainly earned my trust and future business.

reviews.author_name: D A L T O S H O P
reviews.text: I hired GWS Pressure Cleaning to clean my driveway and roof, and the results were amazing. They were punctual, professional, and paid great attention to detail. Everything looks brand new, and they were also very friendly throughout the entire process. I’ll definitely recommend them and use their services again!

SEE UPDATE!! Prompt arrival and easy to communicate with. Pressure cleaned my metal roof, paver driveway and sidewalks. They even clean your windows! Paid attention to small things like curbing and small concrete pads. Would definitely recommend Buddy and his team.
UPDATE - a few days after the job was completed. I had numerous plants dropping leaves and dying some not even near the pressure cleaning. They need to be more careful and maybe cover some areas. They did not respond to my text with pictures of my dead plants. Use caution.
UPDATE#2 - I was contacted and was told I would receive my money back and I could update my review if I wanted. NO MONEY, NO CONTACT I didn’t ask for a complete refund, just to replace completely dead plants $75

Today I had my roof and windows pressure cleaned. The guys that came did an amazing job. They were on time and very professional.
They exceeded my expectations. My gutters were dirty and I originally didn't ask to clean them but these guys noticed they were very dirty and cleaned for me.  That's what I call Customer Service.
I will continue using them and also recommending to my friends and family.

Highly recommended GWS Pressure Cleaning, this is a top notch company.  I dealt with Buddy who was very accommodating and able to do the job next day. Leo & Jorge arrived right on scheduled to clean the roof, both of them were very professional and detailed.  You don’t find companies like GWS very often where they deliver the service requested on schedule and with the professionalism these two gentlemen delivered. They treated the property like their own.  Can’t say enough on how pleased I am and will recommend to friends and neighbors.

Cleaned my house in Kendall, roof, driveway, gutters, windows, pool deck, external walls. In addition they cleaned the A/C and pool pump enclosures, which were not even included in the agreed upon scope of work. Punctual, efficient work, honest price. Buddy, the owner, is responsive and informative, including about the risk of some vegetation getting burned/damaged by the cleaning chemicals. Special thanks to Leo and Jorge. They were very polite, helpful moving some planters around without being asked to and displayed a positive attitude at all times. Would definitely recommend GWS.

reviews.text: A&D was great! I called them on a Tuesday and there were here by Saturday ( pressure wash tile roof). They company is Professional and they provided quality service. In May 2022, I hired A & D pressure cleaning to clean my S tile roof.  I was concerned because my roof was replaced four years ago and I do not want it damaged.  In the past whenever I had my roof pressure cleaned it began leaking.  The tile manufacturer recommends using only water at 1200 psi or less and no chemicals.  Unfortunately there are are no companies that do that work.  A&D pressure cleaning used a solution of 40 to 60% chlorine which they left on the roof.  They sprayed down the plants so they would not be damaged.  I had to go outside because the chlorine odor was burning my lungs.  They said the odor should dissipate with 45 minutes.  As far as the appearance, the roof looks great!  I do not know if the chlorine does any damage to the foam adhesive or underlayment.  It appears that the foam adhesive has turned into a dry hard piece that can easily slide out from under the tile edges.  But when I looked at the before and after photos it looks like it was already like that before the chlorine treatment.  The price was reasonable and it took between one and two hours for a one story 2000 sq. ft. house.
Those guys didn't come to play, they came to slay!! They were on time, efficient courteous, and my roof looks mavelous!!
